\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.6}{\ignorespaces These plots show the same network model as in Figure 2, but with two different comparisons represented by the blue shading in each node. In (A), the light blue shading represents the $R^2$ for each nodewise regression where \textit  {depression} is not included in any of the models, while the dark blue shading shows the $R_{\Delta }^2$ given the models including \textit  {depression} as well as all of its interaction effects. In (B), the models being compared to the moderation models include \textit  {depressed} as a covariate.\relax }}{29}{figure.caption.10}}
